Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It seems as though there is still ongoing transmission of the WPV in both Pakistan and Afghanistan - both having positive environmental samples, and clinical cases in Afghanistan. As for ongoing transmission of cVDPV2 - there have been 2 new clinical cases confirmed in the Congo DR, with dates of onset in January 2018 - both occurring in Provinces previously reported to have had cases during 2017 (Mulongo district, Haut Lomami province, and Manono district, Tanganyika province). In addition, there is repeated mention of the 2 environmental samples that were positive for cVDPV in Somalia, both related to viruses isolated from environmental samples in Somalia in October and November 2017.

The good news is that it is now almost 6 months since the last case of polio attributable to cVDPV2 was identified in Syria - hopefully signaling that interruption of transmission of the virus has occurred.

A map showing the locations of all confirmed cases of polio (both WPV as well as cVDPV associated can be found at: http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now.

HealthMap/ProMED maps of areas with identified poliovirus circulation in the above reports are available at:
Somalia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5689842,125
Tanganyika, Democratic Republic of Congo:<https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5689842,60107
